character_info.first.name: Maya
character_info.second.name: Chris
character_info.newcomb.name: Newcomb
character_info.hayworth.name: Hayworth
character_info.assistant.name: Anthony
character_info.neutral.name: Kayce
snt.opts_order: ["1;You remember. Oh no, she was so annoying. ;You remember. You really liked her back then.","2;You hug her for a long moment.;You shake her hand instead.","3;“Yup. We should hang out! How about we eat lunch together? ;“Yup. It's been a while. I'm still getting settled.”","4;You turn around - you're curious to see who she's talking about.;You try to follow her, but it's too late. ","5;You can't help it. You like him immediately.;You get Maya's point. The guy seems like a jerk.","6;“I can't - gotta go. Maybe tomorrow.”;You really don't want to be late but relunctantly agree to grab snacks.","7;You point to an empty seat. “Sit here, save me the table.”;You nod and wait for her to invite you to her table.","8;You continue looking at your phone.;“So, what's the deal with Chris? Fill me in!”","9;You ask her about hangout spots after school - you need things to do.;You space out and try to sort out your plans for the rest of the day.","10;You still have most of your chips left but you buy the new ones instead.;“Thanks - but I'm still working on this one.” (You like your current chips)","11;You feel happy to see a familiar face and move a bit closer.;You feel uncomfortable and move away slightly.","12;“You owe me now.”;“It's just because she knows my cousin.”","13;“Oh – sure… I'll move your bag to the floor.”  (Stand up and move bag to the floor);“Oh yeah. Move your bag to the floor.”","14;You immediately move over.;You wait for Maya to move. ","15;“Hello, nice meeting you.”;“Hey, nice to meet you.”","16;“She knows my cousin.”;\"She knew me when we were little.”","17;You change the subject. (How can she talk like that?);You nod while giving her a reassuring look. (You feel bad for her)","18;“Actually, I was going to sit there.” (Take the seat);“I'm good wherever. Chris, where do you think I should sit?”","19;“So, Elisa, how is Thomas? What is he up to these days?”;“Newcomb, I heard you have some issues in student council. How is that going…?”","20;You make a note in your planner; “Go tell them I'm interested, please.\"","21;“Thanks - I've auditioned before. I'll definitely reach out if I need help though.”;You (slightly uncomfortably): \"Ok… great.\"","22;You don't feel like it but you were about to go check out the flyers on the bulletin board anyway.;“Ok, wait for me there, Newcomb – I will meet you in a bit.”","23;“Yes – she told me some funny stories from when we were little, and told me to tell you she misses you, Elisa.”;“Yes – she told me some things… But I'd rather keep it between her and I.”","24; “It's ok - I'm fine standing.”;There is a lot of clutter. You move it and sit like she told you.","25;\"We can leave in 5 minutes.”;“Whenever - it's up to you.”","26;You wait to see if Chris offers to walk with you to class.;“Let's go, Chris. We're walking to class.”","27;“She said a few things.” (Tell him everything that Maya told you).;You don't want to get between them, so you change the subject.","28;You sit across the table and change the topic.;You take a seat next to Chris: “I'd love to hear your idea!”","29;“I'm good here. Grab a chair and join us.”;You sit where she directed you.","30;You stand aside while they talk and check your schedule.;You smile politely and wait to introduce yourself.","31;“I'll wait to hear from you, sir.”;“Let's just schedule now. How's Monday, after school?”","32;“No, I'll wait.”;“I'll take a water. Thanks.”","33;You (on your way out): \"Tell Mr. Hayworth I'm free Wednesday morning.” ;“It's fine, I'll wait.”","34;You check your email on your phone: “Is it always that hectic in here?” ;“Looks like you're the real person running the club - everybody really relies on you!”","35;“I think that's pretty common, actually.”;“Wow, they must really like you to have kept you that long!”","36;“Yes, it's much nicer than yesterday.”;“Now I understand why you call this place Green-wood.”","37;You wave back at him to come join you.;You rush over to join him.","38;“Make sure this gets into the script.\";“Oh sorry, can you add this?”","39;You are bored: “Do people like the teachers here?” (Try to make small talk);You want to get to know Anthony: “So, do you like your classes, Anthony?”","40;“I'll try but I have a lot going on right now.”;\"Definitely, we have a lot to talk about.” ","41;“I'm still trying to make it work.”;You tell him everything you've done in the last few weeks.","42;You ask about his favorite parts of the Theater Club.;You look around at the posters on the wall. ","43;It's not what you wanted, but he picked it up already.;\"Actually I'll have this one instead.\"","44;“You seem to get along with everyone in the school.” ;You're bored with the conversation. \"You work with all the students, huh?\"","45;You nervously change the subject: “The donuts from this place are great.”;You (laughing): “Oh yeah, especially Newcomb...”","46;“I really need this club. It's been really tough finding one I like.”;“I'm interested, but I have other options.”","47;You go for a fist bump instead.;You smile and hug him back.","48;“Ugh, I'm tired. I just wanna finish my homework and go home.”;“How's your event planning going? Any more meetings with Newcomb?”","49;You (waving at him to come over): “Anthony, this is Chris. You're welcome to join us.”;You turn away to avoid him but he spots you and comes over to say hi.","50;“Do you know Anthony? Hayworth's assistant?” (Tell Chris about Anthony);“The librarian will come by in a minute.”","51;You (moving away): “Don't be ridiculous.”;You (laughing): “Don't be ridiculous!”","52;You've never done this before, but you'll do it anyway. ;\"I'm sorry, but I can't make it – I have to meet another teacher. Maybe Anthony can do it?”","53;You reluctantly stay late and walk home.;You work hard, but leave on time so you can get a ride home.","54;“Yeah, I knew I would get in.” ;“I wouldn't have gotten in without knowing people.” ","55;“Yes – I am excited to work on some projects with you!”;“We'll see. I have a lot of work.”","56; “Start with this. I'll get you the rest of it later this week.” ;“Oh -- okay. I suppose I'll get to work on that now, then.”","57;You don't want to get involved: “I'll give you privacy. I think we're done, anyway.”;You feel concerned: “Everything alright, Elisa? What is it?”","58;“Ok - we'll talk later.” ;You reach out to hold her shoulder: “Oh no, I'm so sorry.”","59;You get the list of available lockers from the secretary.;“Show me the empty locker next to yours.” ","60;Slightly annoyed, you take a look at the document.;“Can we talk about that later? I need you to help me get some forms filled out now.\"","61;\"Get me the location and I'll let you know by tomorrow.”;\"Let me know when you have more information.\"","62;“I can't, maybe just leave it here and do it tomorrow?”;You hate when he bosses you around, but drop off the supplies anyway.","63;“Let's share the locker. I think we would be great locker buddies.”;“Thanks for the offer, Anthony, but I am actually going to take the locker next to Elisa.”"]
memory.1.question: Who knew a member of your family?
memory.2.question: Who was surprised that you knew Newcomb?
memory.3.question: Who had an empty locker next to them?
memory.4.question: Who walked down the hallway with you?
memory.5.question: Who stayed at school late with you?
memory.6.question: Who used to be Newcomb’s volunteer?
memory.7.question: Who brought you to Newcomb's lunch meeting?
memory.8.question: Who invited you to grab a snack?
memory.9.question: Who walked with you to class after lunch?
memory.10.question: Who did you have a meeting with?
memory.11.question: Who did you meet first when you arrived to school?
memory.12.question: Who walked out of the library as you were entering?
memory.13.question: Who invited you to an acting class?
memory.14.question: Who was sad about their friendship problem?
memory.15.question: Who needed help with their school event idea?
memory.16.question: Who complimented the meal during lunch?
memory.17.question: Who did you use to go to kindergarten with?
memory.18.question: Who asked you to come in during study hall?
memory.19.question: Who gave you the club position?
memory.20.question: Who was reviewing a proposal from the Theatre Club?
memory.21.question: Who did you first see at the acting class?
memory.22.question: Who had an illness in the family?
memory.23.question: Who was Hayworth’s assistant?
memory.24.question: Who joined the bench meetup by the lockers midway?
memory.25.question: Who invited you for lunch at their lunch table?
memory.26.question: Who admired Newcomb the most?
memory.27.question: Who wanted to share a locker with you?
memory.28.question: Who disliked Newcomb?
memory.29.question: Who were you scheduled to meet in their office?
memory.30.question: Who walked you to the classroom where you were meeting Hayworth?
